akas: Pair of Kings - Die Königsbrüder Germany
akas from release info: Pair of Kings - Die Königsbrüder Germany

1.title: The New King, Part 1: Destiny's Child
1.plot: Brady decides to leave to become the man Mikayla needs him to be.

2.title: The New King, Part 2: The Bro-fessor and Mary Ann
2.plot: Boomer teaches Boz the finer points of being a brother.

3.title: Two Kings and a Devil Baby
3.plot: Boz discovers a baby and brings it home with him, only to discover that the baby is actually the infant prince of the Tarantula People, who threaten war unless the baby is returned.

4.title: Fatal Distraction
4.plot: Boomer and Boz tarnish Mikayla's first chance of beating Mason.

5.title: O Lanada
5.plot: Boomer and Boz find out that Lanny is mad at them.

6.title: Kinkowan Summer
6.plot: Boomer organizes a summer vacation cruise for the island teens.

7.title: Heart and Troll
7.plot: King Boz tries to prove to his ex-girlfriend how amazing his new life is.

8.title: I Know What You Did Last Sunday
8.plot: Boz feels pressure to be equally as great as Boomer.

9.title: Lord of the Fries
9.plot: OIne of the Kings' stunts gets Mikayla suspended.

10.title: Dancing with the Scars
10.plot: Boomer wants Boz to enter a dance contest with him.

11.title: I'm Gonna Git You, Sponge Sucka'
11.plot: When Mason thinks Boomer's club is too rowdy, he takes over as head bouncer, but starts to keep the party out. In order to get Mason away from the club, the Kings lead him on a wild goose chase, leaving the club wide open and vulnerable to a mythical human-like sponge creature named Damone, who absorbs everyone's confidence.

12.title: Bond of Brothers
12.plot: Boomer and Boz are each granted one wish on their birthday. Boomer wishes for the island to be danger-free and Boz wishes for the two to be closer, but gets more than he bargained for when they become magnetically attached.

13.title: King vs Wild
13.plot: After all that Boomer has taught Boz about living in the civilized world, Boz decides to address Boomer's lack of survival skills and forces him to go camping. Although Boomer is resistant at first, he has no choice but to become a fast learner and use his newfound skills when the camping trip goes awry, and he needs to help Boz fight for their lives against a jungle werewolf.

14.title: Inconvenient Tooth
14.plot: Boz's monkey antics ruin a double date.

15.title: The Oogli Stick
15.plot: The kings say no to a pair of goat girls who ask them to a dance.

16.title: Thumb & Thumber
16.plot: Boomer believes he is a natural at the dangerous island sport of Thumb War.

17.title: Loathe Potion No. 9
17.plot: Boomer fears that Mikayla and Boz's friendship will blossom into a crush.

18.title: Yeti, Set, Snow
18.plot: The kings are humiliated by a family of mountain yetis.

19.title: Mysteries of Kinkow
19.plot: The Kings learn that secrets have been kept from them.

20.title: Meet the Parent
20.plot: The Kings and Mikayla are in Chicago and meet Boomer's girlfriend.

21.title: Long Live the Kings, Part 1
21.plot: The Bat Medallion that Boz hid in Rebecca's apartment has dragged Rebecca to Kinkow. When Mikayla confiscates the Bat Medallion, Kutamungo captures her and the Bat Medallion in order to revive Kaita the Bat-Rider.

22.title: Long Live the Kings, Part 2
22.plot: Kinkow seems destined for doom when Kaita the Mummy returns.

1.title: Return of the Kings
1.plot: During their coronation as kings of the mystical island of Kinkow, twins Boomer and Brady accidentally destroy a sacred ruby, causing Mount Spew to erupt.

2.title: Return of the Kings: Part Two
2.plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.

3.title: Beach Bully Bingo
3.plot: Brady and Boomer are banned from the beach by the top surfer who is known as "The Big Kahula" who's also known as Hibachi. After being banned from the beach they return and they make an impossible bet with Hibachi that they will beat him in a surf competition and take back the beach. Hibachi states that if he wins, then no one will be able to surf on the island ever again, but him and his friends. Brady and Boomer enlist in a boot camp run by Mason, who attempts to train them so they can learn how to surf, and take the beach back. Mason was formerly the top surfer, ...

4.title: A Mermaid's Tail
4.plot: Brady and Boomer meet some mermaids on the beach.

5.title: Where the Wild Kings Are
5.plot: The twins discover a cute little animal and decide to make him their pet.

6.title: Big Kings on Campus
6.plot: Brady gets jealous when Mikayla starts hanging out with her friend Tristan who is into extreme sports. To impress her, Brady joins school and tries to do extreme sports. Meanwhile, when Boomer and Brady are placed with all the little kids, Boomer becomes attached with the kids.

7.title: The Brady Hunch
7.plot: Boomer becomes good friends with a boy from the Flaji clan, a neighboring tribe that Brady begins to suspect are cannibals and want to have Boomer for dinner, so he hatches a plan and attempts to infiltrate the tribe's village while Mason also gets the crazy cannibal theory in his head

8.title: Junga Ball
8.plot: The guys get ready for the Junga Ball tournament against other islands so Brady becomes the leader of the guards who made the team. When Boomer doesn't get to rule the team as much as Brady, Boomer starts his own team with help from Kinkow's residents. The two teams compete to see which team would represent Kinkow.

9.title: Revenge of the Mummy
9.plot: The mummy gets revived with help from the bat medallion and he starts haunting the kings. The kings try to get it back before Mikayla and Mason find out.

10.title: Oh Brother, Where Arr Thou?
10.plot: The guys use a special map to find treasure with the help of a pirate, but the pirates trap the whole gang and plans to steal the palace.

11.title: No Kings Allowed
11.plot: Brady and Boomer want to join the Riptides, a gang famous for pulling pranks all over the island. Their final test before they will be accepted into the gang is stealing Yamakoshi; Lanny's pet fish.

12.title: Pair of Jokers
12.plot: When Brady and Boomer attempt to pull pranks on the villagers, they go too far and karma comes full circle, just as Mikayla said.

13.title: Pair of Prom Kings
13.plot: Brady and boomer go back to their Chicago high school's prom. Boomer hopes to see a girl he asked out 4 years ago, while Brady hopes they'll be more popular than before.

14.title: Tone Deaf Jam
14.plot: Boomer is excited to sing for the Harvest Festival, thinking he has a great voice. Brady tries to save him without hurting his feelings.

15.title: The Bite Stuff
15.plot: The king's uncle and aunt come to visit when they think that everything is too dangerous. The guys try to prove the kings are safe, but Brady gets bitten by a bug that gives him horrible side effects.

16.title: Brady Battles Boo-Mer
16.plot: Brady tries to prove to Boomer that ghosts exist.

17.title: The King and Eyes
17.plot: The two kings are told that they have to try to win a competition when they attempt to arrange a treaty with an adversary island. The winner receives the reward of a princess, but Brady and Boomer discover she is not a typical princess.

18.title: The King Beneath My Wings
18.plot: To increase their popularity the kings hold a contest, and allow the winner to follow them around.

19.title: Fight School
19.plot: After learning their father was the best warrior in island history, Boomer and Brady enroll in Kinkow Fight School. When Mason gives the kings special treatment, jealousy overcomes Mikayla. Taking Lanny's advice, she decides to test the kings' newfound confidence and skills by pitting them against Atog the Giant. But when Mason finds out, Mikayla tries to get the kings to back down, but it's too late, the kings are eager to prove their inner warrior

20.title: The Trouble with Doubles
20.plot: Boomer and Brady discover Vault 14, a secret vault which protects Kinkow's most mysterious and powerful artifacts including Duplicatus Plantus, a plant that copies anything it touches. The kings make clones of themselves and while they go surfing, they send their doubles to the Kalooki Island Peace Summit. Filling in for the brothers, the clones impress Mikayla, the island dignitaries and the other Kinkowians with their intelligence, hygiene, and professionalism. However, when Brady and Boomer overhear the clones' ultimate plan to takeover, the kings must figure out ...

21.title: Journey to the Center of Mt. Spew
21.plot: Boomer wants to find out whether he or Brady is older, so goes to consult the volcano's oracle. His friends try to stop him as they don't want to lose a king.

1.title: Kings of Legend: Part One
1.plot: When trying to prove they are The Kings of Legand, Brady and Boomer accidentally bring to life an ancient evil statue called Zadoc, thus putting the island in jeopardy.

2.title: Kings of Legend: Part Two
2.plot: Boomer and Brady fight for their lives.

3.title: Good King Hunting
3.plot: After Boomer takes the blame for a note Brady left asking Mikayla for a date, he finds himself being hunted by Mason as part of an ancient Kinkowian tradition.

4.title: Dinner for Squonks
4.plot: The boys find a secret bunker, from where Kinkow secret operations are being run by Mason and Mikayla. The boys insist on taking over, but offend the squonks and must apologize.

5.title: Kings of Thieves
5.plot: The kings overspend causes a tax to be levied on unhappy islanders. Soon sirocco a robin hood style out law emerges. Boomer is amazed when he discovers Siroccos family.

6.title: An Ice Girl for Boomer
6.plot: Brady discovers a beautiful cave girl has thawed after thousands of years.

7.title: Pair of Geniuses
7.plot: Boomer and Brady face an island's curse and must cure it.

8.title: How I Met Your Brother
8.plot: It's Mikayla's birthday and Mason's brother Jason visits, but Mason isn't so welcoming due to an incident when they were kids. When the kings make Jason head guard, Mason quits and drowns his sorrows in eating. But when the Tarantula people try to roast Boomer alive, Jason cowardly runs off and it's up to Brady to convince Mason and his bloated self to come back and save Boomer. When Mason arrives, he and King Brady are captured by tarantula people. The Jason's water scooter falls on two tarantula persons, and Jason falls on other two.

9.title: The One About Mikayla's Friends
9.plot: Brady and Boomer decide to find a female friend for Mikayla.

10.title: Do Over
10.plot: Boomer and Brady find an ancient pocket watch.

11.title: Big Mama Waka
11.plot: Mikayla is sick with Moocoo fever and Brady takes care of her.

12.title: Sleepless in the Castle
12.plot: Brady has developed an unusual sleeping habit - he becomes a sleep ninja.

13.title: Pair of Clubs
13.plot: Boomer opens a hotspot; Brady opens his own club when Boomer fires him.

14.title: The Cheat Life of Brady and Boomer
14.plot: Mikayla agrees to help Brady and Boomer pass the challenge.

16.title: Pair of Santas
16.plot: In an effort to bring their holiday traditions to Kinkow, the kings promise the islanders a Super Christmas and enlist the island elves to make the toys. When the elves revolt, Boomer and Brady must figure out how to save Christmas.

17.title: No Rhyme or Treason
17.plot: Boomer develops a friendship with Mikayla around Kinkowian poetry slams.

18.title: Mr. Boogey Shoes
18.plot: Boomer tells Brady the Boogey Man stole his favorite sneakers.

19.title: The Young and the Restless
19.plot: Boomer and Brady accidentally activate a fountain of youth.

20.title: Let the Clips Show
20.plot: The kings try to prove the explosion in the castle was not their fault.

21.title: Crouching Brady, Hidden Boomer
21.plot: Brady goes on a date with Mikayla's rival from fight school, and the girl challenges Mikayla to a duel.

22.title: Beach Party Maggot Massacre
22.plot: The Kings invite their entire high school class to an epic beach party.

23.title: Make Dirt, Not War
23.plot: Oogie has to hide his relationship with Priscilla, the Dirt Fairy.

24.title: The Evil King
24.plot: When two moons appear, the kings meet the ghost of Malakai, the first king of Kinkow, who explains that an evil twin will destroy the island. This causes things to come between the kings themselves.

25.title: The Evil King Part 2
25.plot: When two moons appear, the kings meet the ghost of Malakai, the first king of Kinkow, who explains that an evil twin will destroy the island. This causes things to come between the kings themselves.

26.title: Cooks Can Be Deceiving
26.plot: The kings are left on their own to take care of a starving Ogre.

locations: Sunset Gower Studios - 1438 N. Gower Street, Hollywood, Los Angeles, California, USA
